The paper discusses two leading approaches for robust optimization in online algorithms and mechanism design, which are both subfields of theoretical computer science. The paper specifically focuses on competitive analysis and prior-independent mechanism design, which are subfields of game theory and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). Additionally, the paper involves algorithmic techniques and optimization, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
